The paper discusses a query engine for statistical relational models, which involves machine learning and data management. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of ILPs, which are commonly used in optimization problems, suggesting the category cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of parallelism and multi-core architectures suggests the category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions experiments with Markov logic network benchmarks, which are commonly used in probabilistic graphical models, suggesting the category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency and quality of results, which are important aspects of database systems, suggesting the category cs.DB (Databases).
